        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 6:30PM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>At 629 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Villages at Sandhill, or 7 miles northeast of
Columbia, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Columbia, Camden, Lake Wateree Dam, Lugoff, Villages at Sandhill,
Elgin, Sesquicentennial State Park, Lake Carolina, Fort Jackson,
Goodale State Park, Oakland, Ridgeway, Dalzell, Dinkins Mill, North
Towne Square Shopping Center, Fort Jackson Wildcat Road, Midway
Elementary School, Boykin, Pine Grove Fire Station, and Smallwood.

This includes Interstate 20 in South Carolina between mile markers 77
and 105.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
